.maincont  
  %h3 Display the Live Streams widget
  %p Embedding the Live Steams list on your page is as easy as 1, 2!
  %br
  %br  
  %h2 1
  %br  
  %p
    To use the Live Streams widget on your band's website, first copy the following code into the
    appropriate position inside the &lt;body&gt; tag. <em>BAND_SHORT_NAME</em> must
    be replaced with the short name of your band, as given in your
    = link_to('band management page', 'me/control_panel') + '.'
  .code
    = %{ <div class='band=BAND_SHORT_NAME' id='mbs-access-schedule-container'> </div> }
  %br
  %br  
  %h2 2
  %br  
  %p
    Paste the following code in the head, just before
    %span.inline-code
      = '</head>'
    in your document. If you have jQuery 1.4.2 already included on your site, you can omit the jQuery include below.
  .code
    = '<script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.4.2/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>'
    %br
    = '<script src="' + root_url + '/javascripts/jquery.fancybox-1.3.1.pack.js" type="text/javascript"></script>'
    %br
    = '<script src="' + root_url + 'javascripts/access_schedule.js" type="text/javascript"></script> '
    %br
    = '<link href="' + root_url + 'stylesheets/lightbox.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />'
    %br
    = '<link href="' + root_url + 'stylesheets/access_schedule.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />'
  %br
  %br  
  %h2 3 (optional)
  %br  
  %p
    Replace the <span class="inline-code">access_schedule.css</span> stylesheet with one of your own,
    to provide custom styling for the Live Streams widget. You can also just keep the above stylesheet include
    and add custom styling after it. Here's an example of a custom widget style:
  %pre.code
    :escaped
      <style>
        #mbs-access-schedule-container {
          border: 5px dashed purple;
          background: url(http://imgur.com/XFG8l.jpg)
                      no-repeat
                      rgb(20%, 80%, 40%);
          font-size: 12pt;
          width: auto;
          height: auto;
        }
      </style>
  
  
